To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Ohio Open Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

Non-exempt audio, video (including body-worn camera, in-car "dash cam", surveillance video, etc), and written reports compiled or obtained by your department related to the response and investigation into the incident below.

Incident: 6/6/22, woman jumps from ambulance and is seriously injured. Location was in the 4200 block of Amelia Olive Branch Road. For reference: https://www.fox19.com/2022/06/07/woman-jumps-ambulance-gets-stuck-under-it-clermont-county-dispatchers-say/

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Patrick Wells

title: Los Angeles Sheriff's Department - Field Operations Directives

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

I am seeking information relating to the following Field Operations Directives (FODs) or Field Operations Support Services (FOSS) newsletters:

89-007 Prosecution of Street Gang Members
89-006 Gang Member Release Policy
10-001 Gang Injunctions
01-003 Proposition 21 Gang Registration
FOSS-21-15 Field Interview Cards

For each of these FOD or FOSS newsletters I am seeking:

1. The date that the new policy was implemented and issued.
2. The date that the old policy that was replaced (if applicable) was first implemented.
2. A copy of the previous policy that was replaced (if applicable) by the current policy in place, including any old copies of the Field Interview cards and when they were discontinued.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Justin Seitz

title: Calumet City Police Department: Citations to journalist

communications.subject: Illinois Freedom of Information Act. Request: Calumet City Police Department: Citations to journalist
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

1. Any citation issued to Hank Sanders since October 1, 2023.

2. Any police incident report, narrative, or complaint concerning Hank Sanders since September 1, 2023. This includes any complaint made by or on behalf of Thaddeus Jones, Jerico Thomas, or Megan Wilson, as reported by the Chicago Tribune: https://www.chicagotribune.com/news/breaking/ct-calumet-city-tribune-reporter-citations-20231102-ts6ugr2t6vdahap72yw2s7gkoi-story.html.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Adam Steinbaugh
